WEBVTT

00:01.300 --> 00:02.619
Previously on Hannibal

00:02.670 --> 00:04.661
- You make jumps
you can't explain, Will.

00:04.700 --> 00:08.067
- The evidence explains.
- Then help me find
some evidence.

00:08.100 --> 00:11.103
- I wouldn't put him out there!
- Should he get too close,
I need you to make sure

00:11.140 --> 00:14.678
he's not out there alone.
- I don't think the Shrike
killed that girl in the field.

00:14.710 --> 00:17.201
This girl's killer thought
that she was a pig.

00:17.250 --> 00:21.243
- You think this was a copycat?
- I think I can help good Will
see his face.

00:21.280 --> 00:23.748
- Hello?
- They know.

00:23.790 --> 00:25.781
(gunshots)

00:26.560 --> 00:28.710
- You said he wouldn't get
too close.

00:28.760 --> 00:31.456
- See?

00:38.370 --> 00:44.366
(gunshots)

01:07.130 --> 01:09.826
(Hobbs' daughter gasping)

01:09.870 --> 01:11.497
- (Hobbs): See?

01:11.530 --> 01:14.465
(Hobbs' daughter gasping)
See?

01:21.310 --> 01:23.107
- We're here.

01:28.480 --> 01:31.483
(police radio chatter)

02:40.790 --> 02:42.451
- Could be

02:42.490 --> 02:46.221
a permanent installation
in your Evil Minds Museum.

02:46.260 --> 02:48.899
- Well, what we learn
about Garrett Jacob Hobbs will

02:48.930 --> 02:51.364
help us catch the next one
like him.

02:51.400 --> 02:54.631
There's still seven bodies
unaccounted for.

02:54.670 --> 02:57.503
- Yeah, well,
he was eating them.

02:57.540 --> 02:59.770
- Had to be some parts
he wasn't eating.

02:59.810 --> 03:03.268
- Not necessarily.

03:03.310 --> 03:06.939
- All right, what if Hobbs
wasn't eating alone?
It's a lot of work.

03:06.980 --> 03:09.778
Disappearing these girls,
butchering them, and then

03:09.820 --> 03:12.380
not leaving a shred of anything
other than what's in this room.

03:12.420 --> 03:15.287
- Someone he hunted with.
- Someone who IS In a coma,

03:15.320 --> 03:19.324
who also happened to be someone
he hunted with.

03:30.340 --> 03:32.308
- Abigail Hobbs is a suspect?

03:32.340 --> 03:34.706
- We've been conducting
house-to-house interviews

03:34.740 --> 03:38.346
at the Hobbs residence,
and, uh, at this property also.

03:41.880 --> 03:45.338
Hobbs spent a lot of time here.
Spent a lot of time

03:45.390 --> 03:46.755
with his daughter here.

03:46.790 --> 03:48.883
She would make the ideal bait,
wouldn't she?

03:48.920 --> 03:51.480
- Hobbs killed alone.

04:08.080 --> 04:11.538
Ah. Someone else was here.

05:13.940 --> 05:16.909
(applause)

05:16.950 --> 05:18.906
- Thank you.

05:18.950 --> 05:20.941
Please stop that.

05:32.130 --> 05:35.554
This is how I caught
Garrett Jacob Hobbs.

05:35.600 --> 05:38.967
It's his resignation letter.

05:39.000 --> 05:41.332
Does anybody see the clue?

05:44.770 --> 05:46.101
There isn't one.

05:46.140 --> 05:47.835
He wrote a letter,

05:47.880 --> 05:51.839
he left a phone number,
no address. That's it.

05:51.880 --> 05:54.849
Bad bookkeeping and dumb luck.

06:04.990 --> 06:07.891
(gasping)

06:16.570 --> 06:20.609
how to stop those
his story is going to inspire.

06:20.640 --> 06:25.145
(projector click)
He's already got one admirer.

06:25.180 --> 06:27.819
A copycat.

06:44.700 --> 06:46.065
Hi.

06:46.100 --> 06:48.136
- How are you, Will?

06:48.170 --> 06:52.038
- Uh, I have no idea.

06:52.070 --> 06:54.038
- Um, I didn't want you
to be ambushed.

06:54.080 --> 06:55.877
- This is an ambush?

06:55.910 --> 06:57.468
- Ambush is later.

06:57.510 --> 06:59.740
Immediately later--
soon to now.

06:59.780 --> 07:01.873
When Jack arrives,
consider yourself ambushed.

07:01.920 --> 07:03.740
- Here's Jack.

07:03.790 --> 07:06.588
- How was class?
- Um, they applauded.

07:06.620 --> 07:08.986
It was inappropriate.
- Well, the review board would

07:09.020 --> 07:12.490
beg to differ. You're up for a
commendation. And they've, uh,

07:12.530 --> 07:14.589
okayed active return
to the field.

07:14.630 --> 07:16.120
- The question is,

07:16.160 --> 07:19.493
do you want to go back
to the field?

07:19.540 --> 07:21.963
- I want him back
in the field.

07:22.000 --> 07:24.901
And I've told the board
I'm recommending a psych eval.

07:24.940 --> 07:27.909
- Are we starting now?

07:27.940 --> 07:30.170
- Oh, the session wouldn't be
with me.

07:30.210 --> 07:33.919
- Hannibal Lecter's a better
fit. Your relationship's
not personal.

07:33.950 --> 07:36.919
But if you are more comfortable
with Dr. Bloom...

07:36.950 --> 07:39.919
- I'm not comfortable with
anybody inside my head.

07:39.960 --> 07:43.179
- You've never killed anyone
before, Will.

07:43.230 --> 07:45.790
It's a deadly force encounter.
It's a lot to digest.

07:45.830 --> 07:47.559
- I used to work Homicide.

07:47.600 --> 07:49.898
- The reason you currently
USED to work Homicide is because

07:49.930 --> 07:52.694
you didn't have the stomach
for pulling the trigger.

07:52.740 --> 07:55.937
You just pulled the trigger
10 times.

07:55.970 --> 07:59.030
- Wait, so a psych eval isn't
a formality?

07:59.070 --> 08:01.903
- No, it's so I can get
some sleep at night. I asked you

08:01.940 --> 08:04.204
to get close to the Hobbs thing.
I need to know you didn't get

08:04.250 --> 08:07.674
too close. How many nights did
you spend in Abigail Hobbs'

08:07.720 --> 08:09.711
hospital room, Will?

08:12.590 --> 08:14.581
- Therapy doesn't work on me.

08:17.890 --> 08:22.224
- Therapy doesn't work on you
because you won't let it.
- And because I know

08:22.260 --> 08:25.525
all the tricks.
- Well, perhaps you need
to un-learn some tricks.

08:25.570 --> 08:27.697
- Why not have a conversation
with Hannibal?

08:27.740 --> 08:30.732
He was there. He knows
what you went through.

08:33.110 --> 08:35.203
- Come on, Will.

08:35.240 --> 08:37.970
I need my beauty sleep!

08:47.860 --> 08:49.680
- What's that?

08:49.730 --> 08:54.258
- Your psychological evaluation.
You are totally functional and

08:54.300 --> 08:56.825
more or less sane. Well done.

08:56.870 --> 08:59.691
- Did you just rubber stamp me?

08:59.740 --> 09:01.890
- Yes. Jack Crawford may lay his

09:01.940 --> 09:04.033
weary head to rest
knowing he didn't break you

09:04.070 --> 09:06.777
and our conversation can proceed
unobstructed by paperwork.

09:09.780 --> 09:13.147
- Jack thinks
that I need therapy.

09:13.180 --> 09:17.719
- What you need is
a way out of dark places
when Jack sends you there.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.786
- Last time he sent me
Into a dark place,

09:19.820 --> 09:21.253
I brought something back.

09:21.290 --> 09:23.827
- A surrogate daughter?

09:27.100 --> 09:29.921
You saved Abigail Hobbs' life.
You also orphaned her.

09:29.970 --> 09:32.188
That comes with certain
emotional obligations,

09:32.230 --> 09:34.937
regardless of empathy disorders.
- You were there.

09:34.970 --> 09:37.200
You saved her life too.
Do you feel obligated?

09:39.210 --> 09:41.269
- Yes.

09:41.310 --> 09:44.871
I feel a staggering amount
of obligation.

09:44.910 --> 09:46.912
I feel responsibility.

09:48.920 --> 09:51.787
I've fantasized about scenarios
where my actions may have

09:51.820 --> 09:53.959
allowed a different fate
for Abigail Hobbs.

09:58.730 --> 10:01.949
- Jack thinks Abigail Hobbs
helped her dad kill those girls.

10:04.830 --> 10:06.798
- How does that make you feel?

10:06.840 --> 10:08.967
- How does it make you feel?

10:09.000 --> 10:12.060
- I find it vulgar.
- Me too.

10:12.110 --> 10:13.975
- And entirely possible.

10:14.010 --> 10:16.808
- It's not what happened.
- Jack will ask her

10:16.850 --> 10:19.171
when she wakes up, or he'll have
one of us ask her.

10:19.210 --> 10:21.974
- Is this therapy,
or a support group?

10:22.020 --> 10:25.945
- It's whatever you need it
to be.

10:27.960 --> 10:29.780
And, Will,

10:29.830 --> 10:32.924
the mirrors in your mind can
reflect the best of yourself,

10:32.960 --> 10:35.019
not the worst of someone else.

10:58.150 --> 11:00.755
What is that?

11:02.760 --> 11:04.318
- I bet it's marijuana.

11:04.360 --> 11:07.852
- Mushrooms. Look, they got
tubes to water 'em or something.

11:07.900 --> 11:09.424
- No, it's a marijuana plant.

11:13.770 --> 11:15.897
- That's not marijuana.

11:39.360 --> 11:42.761
(gunshots)

11:51.510 --> 11:53.375
- I'm pretty sure

11:53.410 --> 11:56.379
firearm accuracy isn't
a prerequisite for teaching.

11:56.410 --> 11:58.446
- Well, I've been
in the field before.

11:58.480 --> 12:03.281
- Now you're back
in the saddle. Ish.
-Ishindeed.

12:03.320 --> 12:06.414
Took me 10 shots
to drop Hobbs.

12:06.450 --> 12:09.954
- Zeller wanted to give you
the bullets he pulled out of
Hobbs in an acrylic case, but

12:09.990 --> 12:12.151
I told him you wouldn't
think it was funny.

12:12.190 --> 12:15.125
- Probably not.
- I suggested one of those

12:15.160 --> 12:17.390
clackin' swingin'
ball things.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.991
- That would've
been funny.

12:31.550 --> 12:35.077
- You're a Weaver. I took you
for an isosceles guy.

12:35.120 --> 12:38.089
- I have a rotator cuff issue so
I have to use the Weaver stance.

12:38.120 --> 12:40.350
- You are tight.

12:40.390 --> 12:42.312
- I got stabbed
when I was a cop.

12:42.360 --> 12:44.419
- Yeah, I got stabbed
in the third grade

12:44.460 --> 12:47.850
with a number two pencil.
Thought I was gonna get
lead poisoning.

12:47.900 --> 12:50.460
- Uh, no lead in pencils;
it's graphite.

12:50.500 --> 12:53.537
- See if that helps
with the recoil.

13:03.980 --> 13:05.538
- That was better.

13:05.580 --> 13:08.913
You come all the way down here
to teach me how to shoot?

13:16.120 --> 13:18.156
(crow cawing)

13:35.510 --> 13:39.105
- So, Lecter gave you
the all-clear.

13:39.150 --> 13:41.471
Therapy might work on you
after all.

13:41.520 --> 13:45.342
- Therapy is an acquired taste
which I have yet to acquire.

13:45.390 --> 13:49.087
But, uh, it served your purpose.
I'm back in the field.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.849
- Local police found

13:50.890 --> 13:53.495
tire tracks
on a hidden service road

13:53.530 --> 13:56.124
and some small animal traps
in the surrounding area.

13:56.160 --> 13:58.526
- He wanted to keep his crop
undisturbed.

13:58.570 --> 14:00.891
- The only thing missing is
the scarecrow.

14:04.310 --> 14:08.269
- OK, we've got nine bodies,
various stages of decay,
and as you can see,

14:08.310 --> 14:10.540
all very well fertilized.

14:10.580 --> 14:14.141
_ -_ He buri_ed them
In a high-nutrient compost.

14:14.180 --> 14:16.546
He was enthusiastically
encouraging decomposition.

14:16.580 --> 14:18.889
- They were buried alive with
the intention of keeping them

14:18.920 --> 14:21.286
that way--I mean,
for a little while.

14:21.320 --> 14:25.120
- (Jimmy): Long enough
for the fungus to eat away any
distinguishing characteristics.

14:25.160 --> 14:27.128
- Line and rebar were used

14:27.160 --> 14:30.994
to administer intravenous fluids
after they were buried.

14:31.030 --> 14:33.294
He was feeding them
something.

14:33.340 --> 14:37.436
- No restraints?

14:37.470 --> 14:40.439
- Just dirt.
- The other end
of the air-supply system

14:40.480 --> 14:42.129
comes up over there.

14:42.180 --> 14:44.341
It isn't a very considerate
clean air solution,

14:44.380 --> 14:48.043
which clearly wasn't a priority,
'cause he isn't lazy.

14:48.080 --> 14:51.208
- No, he's not.

14:56.990 --> 14:58.628
- You find any shitakes?

14:58.660 --> 15:01.197
- (Jimmy): No.

15:01.230 --> 15:03.221
- Welcome back.

15:11.470 --> 15:14.678
- Tell Sam to give me a call,
will you? Thank you.

15:19.980 --> 15:22.346
- Excuse me.
I'm one of the parents

15:22.380 --> 15:24.712
of the explorers
who found the bodies.

15:24.750 --> 15:27.310
I wanted to thank you for being
so good with all the boys.

15:27.360 --> 15:30.579
- Those boys were very brave.
- They are good boys.
- Yeah.

15:30.630 --> 15:34.350
- You're a local
police detective?
- Yes ma'am.

15:34.400 --> 15:36.960
- Would it be an imposition
to ask a few things?

15:37.000 --> 15:39.969
The boys are gonna have
questions and I just want
to be as honest with them as--

15:40.000 --> 15:42.662
- Of course.
- Can you, uh,

15:42.700 --> 15:45.498
tell me what that man is doing
over there by himself?

15:45.540 --> 15:47.599
- He's some kind
of specral consultant.

15:47.640 --> 15:50.404
Works for the FBI.
- Huh.

16:06.130 --> 16:08.121
(sound muted)

16:10.700 --> 16:14.431
(soft ambient pulse)

16:56.610 --> 16:59.078
(Sound returns.)

17:03.090 --> 17:06.139
- I do not bind his arms
or legs

17:06.190 --> 17:09.557
as I bury him
in a shallow grave.

17:09.590 --> 17:13.822
(ventilator pumping)

17:13.860 --> 17:16.192
He's alive.

17:16.230 --> 17:19.324
But he will never
be conSCIous again.

17:27.510 --> 17:29.569
He won't know that he's dying.

17:31.580 --> 17:33.343
I don't need him to.

17:36.250 --> 17:38.241
This is my design.

17:48.530 --> 17:51.090
- I think your family's leaving.
- We drove separately.

17:51.130 --> 17:54.361
(muffled gasp)
(Will gasping)

17:54.400 --> 17:56.732
- (Will): I need an EMT!

17:56.770 --> 18:01.400
(person gasping)

18:01.440 --> 18:04.500
- (Katz): EMT! We need an EMT!
- (Zeller): Don't touch him!

18:12.550 --> 18:14.654
- This may have been premature.

18:16.660 --> 18:20.653
- What did you see?
Out in the field.

18:22.830 --> 18:24.491
- Hobbs.

18:24.530 --> 18:25.895
- An association?

18:25.930 --> 18:27.534
- A hallucination.

18:27.570 --> 18:30.437
I saw him lying there
in someone else's grave.

18:30.470 --> 18:33.507
- Did you tell Jack
what you saw?

18:33.540 --> 18:35.679
- No.

18:35.710 --> 18:38.270
- It's stress.

18:38.310 --> 18:39.846
Not worth reporting.

18:39.880 --> 18:43.247
You displaced the victim
of another killer's crime

18:43.290 --> 18:46.384
with what could arguably be
considered your victim.

18:46.420 --> 18:48.684
- I don't consider Hobbs
my VIctIm.

18:48.720 --> 18:52.429
- What do you consider him?

18:52.460 --> 18:54.451
- Dead.

18:57.700 --> 19:00.794
- Is it harder
imagining the thrill
somebody else feels killing,

19:00.840 --> 19:03.434
now that you've done it
yourself?

19:17.520 --> 19:18.885
The arms.

19:18.920 --> 19:23.289
Why did he leave them exposed?
To hold their hands?

19:23.330 --> 19:25.548
To feel the life
leaving their bodies?

19:25.590 --> 19:29.629
- No, that's too esoteric for
someone who_too_k _the time
to bury his Victims

19:29.660 --> 19:32.299
in a straight line.
He's more practical.

19:32.330 --> 19:34.639
- He was cultivating them.
- He was keeping them alive.

19:34.670 --> 19:36.638
He was feeding them
intravenously.

19:36.670 --> 19:39.662
- But your farmer let his crops
die. Save for the one
that didn't.

19:39.710 --> 19:42.304
- Well, and the one that didn't
died on the way to the hospital,

19:42.340 --> 19:44.706
though they weren't crops;
they were the fertilizer. The
bodies were covered in fungus.

19:44.750 --> 19:48.572
- The structure
of a fungus mirrors
that of the human brain--

19:48.620 --> 19:50.986
an intricate_ web
of connections.

19:51.020 --> 19:55.514
- So maybe he admires
their ability to connect

19:55.560 --> 19:57.528
the way human minds can't.

19:57.560 --> 20:00.358
- Yours can.
(Will laughs.)

20:00.400 --> 20:03.392
- Yep. Um... yeah,
not physically.

20:05.400 --> 20:07.561
- Is that what your farmer is
looking for?

20:07.600 --> 20:09.761
Some sort of connection?

20:12.040 --> 20:14.235
- (Will): Goodbye.

20:23.520 --> 20:25.488
- Miss Kimball?
- Yes.

20:25.520 --> 20:27.249
- Good evening. Please come in.

20:40.400 --> 20:41.162
- I'v
8,

20:41.200 --> 20:43.907
uh, never seen
a psychiatrist before.

20:43.940 --> 20:47.569
And I am unfortunately
thorough,

20:47.610 --> 20:51.808
so you're one of three doctors
I'm interviewing.

20:51.850 --> 20:54.318
It's more or less
a bake-off.

20:54.350 --> 20:56.443
- I'm very supportive
of bake-offs.

20:56.480 --> 20:58.539
It's important you find someone
you're comfortable with.

20:58.590 --> 21:01.718
- I can imagine you
as my therapist,

21:01.760 --> 21:03.751
which is good.

21:03.790 --> 21:07.920
If_I can't visualize
opening up emotionally,
I know it would be a problem.

21:07.960 --> 21:09.928
- May I ask why now?

21:09.960 --> 21:12.428
- Do you mind ifI ask you

21:12.470 --> 21:15.598
a few questions first?
- Of course not.

21:15.640 --> 21:18.859
- I love that you've written
so much on social exclusion.

21:18.910 --> 21:21.572
Since that's why I'm here,
I was wondering--

21:21.610 --> 21:23.601
- Are you Freddie Lounds?

21:27.620 --> 21:31.317
This is unethical,
even for a tabloid journalist.

21:31.350 --> 21:33.318
- I am, uh,

21:33.360 --> 21:35.487
I am so embarrassed.

21:37.490 --> 21:39.754
- I'm afraid I must ask
for your bag.

21:39.790 --> 21:41.849
- What?

21:41.900 --> 21:43.458
- Your bag.

21:43.500 --> 21:46.992
Please hand it over.

21:47.030 --> 21:49.362
I'd rather not take it
from you.

21:52.010 --> 21:54.604
Thank you.

21:57.040 --> 21:59.702
- I was recording
our conversation.

21:59.750 --> 22:02.116
- Our conversation?
Yours and mine?

22:02.150 --> 22:04.015
- Yes.

22:04.050 --> 22:06.041
- No other conversation?

22:06.090 --> 22:07.682
- No.

22:09.690 --> 22:11.885
- You were very persistent
about your appointment time.

22:11.930 --> 22:14.626
How did you know
when Will Graham would be here?

22:14.660 --> 22:16.992
- I may have also recorded
your session with Will Graham.

22:17.030 --> 22:18.998
- You didn't answer
the question. How did you know?

22:19.030 --> 22:22.397
- I can't answer
that question.

22:24.770 --> 22:26.931
- Come. Sit by me.

22:34.020 --> 22:36.716
Delete the conversations
you recorded.

22:36.750 --> 22:39.878
Doctor-patient confidentiality
works both ways.

22:41.890 --> 22:43.881
Delete it, please.

22:51.630 --> 22:55.134
You've been terribly rude,
Miss Lounds.

22:58.170 --> 23:00.968
What's to be done
about that?

23:03.480 --> 23:06.608
***
