Cello Suite No.4: Prelude)

23:06.650 --> 23:09.642
Loin, served with a Cumberland
sauce of red fruits.

23:09.680 --> 23:11.989
- Um, loin. What kind?

23:12.020 --> 23:15.183
- Pork.
- Wonderful.

23:15.220 --> 23:19.429
I don't get many opportunities
to, uh, eat home-cooked meals.

23:19.460 --> 23:23.669
My wife and I both work, and,
uh, as hard as I tried not to,

23:23.700 --> 23:26.464
I did wind up
marrying my mother.

23:26.500 --> 23:29.560
- Your mother didn't cook?

23:29.600 --> 23:31.704
- She did, she did.

23:31.740 --> 23:33.139
I only wish she didn't.

23:33.170 --> 23:35.206
There was this meal

23:35.240 --> 23:37.708
she used to prepare. She liked
to call it "oriental noodles".

23:37.750 --> 23:42.016
Spaghetti, soy sauce,
bouillon cubes, and spam.

23:42.050 --> 23:44.712
I was raised thin
as a youngster.

23:44.750 --> 23:46.843
- Well, next time,
bring your wife.

23:46.890 --> 23:49.814
I'd love to have you
both for dinner.

23:49.860 --> 23:51.589
- Thank you.

23:51.630 --> 23:53.120
Mmm.

23:53.160 --> 23:56.755
Lovely. So, why do you think
Will Graham

23:56.800 --> 23:58.722
came back to see you?
- I'm sure

23:58.770 --> 24:01.637
he recognizes the necessity
of his own support structure

24:01.670 --> 24:03.638
if he is to go on supporting
you in the field.

24:03.670 --> 24:05.638
- Well, I believe that a guy
like Will Graham knows

24:05.670 --> 24:07.638
exactly what's going on
inside of his head,

24:07.680 --> 24:09.898
