31:02.360 --> 31:04.555
- And evidently did.
- Sure did.

31:04.590 --> 31:07.559
- You know, the unfortunate
timing of your article allowed

31:07.590 --> 31:09.592
a murderer to escape.

31:13.300 --> 31:15.666
You were in Minnesota.

31:15.700 --> 31:19.033
You were in the Shrike's nest.
You know how I know?

31:19.070 --> 31:21.334
'Cause you left one
of these hairs behind.

31:21.380 --> 31:23.336
You contaminated
the crime scene.

31:23.380 --> 31:25.598
Just like everywhere you go,
you contaminate crime scenes.

31:25.650 --> 31:28.471
That's obstructing justice.
I can indict you

31:28.520 --> 31:31.318
for obstructing justice.

31:31.350 --> 31:34.911
- I'd appreciate it
if you didn't.

31:34.960 --> 31:37.053
- You don't write another word
about Will Graham

31:37.090 --> 31:39.058
and I won't have to.

31:49.100 --> 31:51.409
- (Zeller): You used me.

31:53.670 --> 31:57.401
(monitor beeping)
(ventilator pumping)

32:07.290 --> 32:11.522
(footsteps)

32:58.710 --> 33:03.409
- "He and the Grandmother
discussed better times.
The old lady said that

33:03.440 --> 33:06.273
"in her opinion,
Europe was entirely

33:06.310 --> 33:08.414
to blame for the way things were
now. She said--"

33:08.450 --> 33:10.042
- What are you reading?

33:15.320 --> 33:18.027
- Flannery O'Connor.

33:18.060 --> 33:20.358
When I was Abigail's age,

33:20.390 --> 33:22.426
I was obsessed. I even tried
to raise peacocks

33:22.460 --> 33:25.258
because she raised peacocks.

33:25.300 --> 33:28.189
But... they were
really stupid birds.

33:30.200 --> 33:32.236
- You could be reading
to a killer.

33:32.270 --> 33:37.037
- Innocent until guilty
and all that.

33:37.080 --> 33:39.207
I'm about to broach the subject

33:39.250 --> 33:44.142
of that "Takes One
to Know One" article.

33:44.190 --> 33:46.681
- Oh, that.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.688
Did Jack send you?

33:48.720 --> 33:52.087
- No, I sent me.

33:54.160 --> 33:58.699
- I don't think we've ever been
alone in a room together,
have we?

33:58.730 --> 34:01.699
- I haven't noticed.
Have we?

34:01.740 --> 34:05.608
Not that we're
necessarily alone now.

34:05.640 --> 34:08.279
- Yeah, right. Back to...

34:08.310 --> 34:12.349
"Jack Crawford's crime gimp".
- It certainly creates an image.

34:12.380 --> 34:14.575
I don't need to talk about it

34:14.620 --> 34:17.214
if you don't.
- No, no, we can talk about

34:17.250 --> 34:20.640
or not talk about
whatever you want.

34:24.260 --> 34:26.228
Actually, I was...

34:26.260 --> 34:29.229
I was just enjoying
listening to you read.

34:32.270 --> 34:35.535
- Abigail Hobbs is a success
for you.

34:40.670 --> 34:43.878
- She doesn't look
like a success.

34:43.910 --> 34:47.243
- Don't feel sorry
for yourself

34:47.280 --> 34:50.511
because you saved
this girl's life.
- I don't.

34:50.550 --> 34:54.384
I don't feel sorry for myself
at all.

34:54.420 --> 34:57.514
Ifeel, um...

34:57.560 --> 34:59.528
I-I...

34:59.560 --> 35:01.289
Ifeel, um...

35:04.830 --> 35:06.695
...good.

35:46.710 --> 35:49.679
- Don't know where you got
half that information.
It wasn't from me.

35:49.710 --> 35:52.178
- I may have made
some inferences.

35:52.210 --> 35:54.747
- They think I told you
all of it.

35:54.780 --> 35:56.748
- They saw you talking to me.

35:56.780 --> 36:00.216
- They think it's my fault
Stammets escaped.

36:00.250 --> 36:02.616
- I'm sorry I got you fired.
- I wasn't fired.

36:02.660 --> 36:05.458
I was suspended.
- They're gonna fire you.

36:05.490 --> 36:07.583
Jack Crawford will make sure
of that.

36:07.630 --> 36:09.427
- You...

36:09.460 --> 36:12.725
you stir the hornet's nest,
and I'm the one who gets stung?

36:12.770 --> 36:16.297
- I can help you get work
outside the force,
if you want me to.

36:16.340 --> 36:19.264
I know people
in private security.

36:21.280 --> 36:23.703
- Not the first cop
you got fired.

36:23.740 --> 36:25.970
- Guarantee you it pays better.
Right now,

36:26.010 --> 36:28.513
future you is thanking me.

36:30.880 --> 36:33.485
- I read your article.

36:33.520 --> 36:36.512
Tell me about Will Graham.

36:47.530 --> 36:49.498
- (Lounds): Hey, Jack.

36:49.540 --> 36:53.408
- Miss Lounds?

36:53.440 --> 36:57.979
Go ahead and stand down,
officer. Miss Lounds,
are you all right?

36:58.010 --> 36:59.272
- Where's Will Graham?

36:59.310 --> 37:01.517
- We have an eyewitness
to the murder. We don't need
Will Graham.

37:01.550 --> 37:04.246
- No, that's not why I'm asking.

37:04.350 --> 37:05.783
- Someone find me Will Graham!

37:07.420 --> 37:09.957
This is about Will?
- He was talking about people

37:09.990 --> 37:12.788
having the same properties
of a fungus.
- Stammets?

37:12.830 --> 37:16.391
- Thoughts leaping
from brain to brain.
They mutate, they evolve.

37:16.430 --> 37:21.265
- Well, what does
he want with Will Graham?
- Someone who understands him.

37:21.300 --> 37:24.269
Graham was right. Stammets is
looking for connections.

37:24.310 --> 37:25.834
- What did you tell him?

37:27.840 --> 37:29.535
I need to know

37:29.580 --> 37:32.902
what you told Eldon Stammets
about Will Graham.

37:32.950 --> 37:34.918
- I told him
about the Hobbs girl.

37:34.950 --> 37:37.271
- What did you tell him?

37:37.320 --> 37:39.686
- Everything.

37:39.720 --> 37:42.848
He wants to help Will Graham
connect with Abigail Hobbs.

37:42.890 --> 37:45.381
He's gonna bury her.

37:45.430 --> 37:46.954
(ding!)

37:46.990 --> 37:48.992
- Sorry.

38:09.480 --> 38:11.448
(ding!)

38:11.490 --> 38:14.914
(phone ringing)

38:14.960 --> 38:16.916
- Hello?
- [It's Jack.]

38:16.960 --> 38:18.928
[Are you at the hospital?]
- Yes, I am.

38:18.960 --> 38:21.952
- [Stammets knows
about Abigail Hobbs.]

38:41.110 --> 38:44.546
- Where is she? Abigail Hobbs,
the girl in 408. Where is she?

38:44.590 --> 38:46.649
- They took her for tests.
- Who took her?

38:46.690 --> 38:49.352
Who took her?!

39:02.970 --> 39:05.029
Hey!

39:07.540 --> 39:09.929
(grunting in pain)

39:22.790 --> 39:25.384
What were you gonna do to her?

39:25.430 --> 39:27.921
- We all evolved
from mycelium.

39:27.960 --> 39:29.928
I'm simply reintroducing her
to the concept.

39:29.960 --> 39:31.928
- By burying her alive?

39:31.970 --> 39:34.438
- The journalist said
you understood me.

39:34.470 --> 39:36.097
- I don't.

39:36.140 --> 39:38.859
- Well, you would have.

39:38.910 --> 39:41.470
You would have.

39:41.510 --> 39:43.603
If you walk through a field
of mycelium,

39:43.640 --> 39:45.801
they know you are there.
They know you are there.

39:45.850 --> 39:50.469
The spores reach for you
as you walk by.

39:52.850 --> 39:55.785
I know who you're reaching for.
I know.

39:55.820 --> 39:58.459
Abigail Hobbs.

39:58.490 --> 40:00.754
And you should have let me
plant her.

40:00.790 --> 40:03.497
You would have found her
in a field,

40:03.530 --> 40:06.169
where she was finally able
to reach back!

40:10.470 --> 40:13.109
- (Lecter): When you shot
Eldon Stammets,

40:13.140 --> 40:15.108
who was it that you saw?

40:15.140 --> 40:19.099
- I didn't see Hobbs.

40:19.150 --> 40:22.449
- Then it's not Hobbs' ghost
that's haunting you, is it?

40:22.480 --> 40:25.119
It's the inevitability

40:25.150 --> 40:29.109
of there being a man so bad
that killing him felt good.

40:29.160 --> 40:31.458
- Killing Hobbs felt just.

40:33.760 --> 40:35.728
- Which is why
you're here--

40:35.760 --> 40:37.990
to prove that sprig of zest
you feel is

40:38.030 --> 40:40.464
from saving Abigail,
not from killing her dad.

40:40.500 --> 40:44.869
- I didn't feel a sprig of zest
when I shot Eldon Stammets.

40:44.910 --> 40:47.162
- You didn't kill
Eldon Stammets.

40:51.780 --> 40:54.874
- I thought about it.

40:54.920 --> 40:57.878
I'm still not entirely sure
that wasn't my intention

40:57.920 --> 41:00.013
pulling the trigger.

41:00.050 --> 41:02.154
- If your intention was
to kill him,

41:02.190 --> 41:05.626
it's because you understand
why he did the things he did.

41:05.660 --> 41:09.721
_ It's beautiful
in its own way--

41:09.760 --> 41:13.491
giving voice
to the unmentionable.

41:13.530 --> 41:17.136
- I should've stuck to fixing
boat motors in Louisiana.

41:17.170 --> 41:22.130
- A boat engine is a machine,
a predictable problem,
easy to solve.

41:22.180 --> 41:25.274
You fail, there's a paddle.
Where was your paddle
with Hobbs?

41:25.310 --> 41:29.644
- You're supposed
to be my paddle.
-Iam.

41:29.680 --> 41:34.185
It wasn't the act of killing
